## Invite to Account

Managers can be invited to unclaimed accounts by using this endpoint.

### HTTP Request
`POST <%=@api_prefix%>/2/account/{account_id}/invite`

> Example Requests

```shell
curl -X POST <%=@api_prefix%>/2/account/35/invite \
 -H "W-Token: <%=@wiw_token%>" \
 -data '{"email_or_phone":"9525551234","manager_name":"Sally Smith","message":"This scheduling app is really slick!"}'
```
```php
<?php
$wiw = new Wheniwork("<%=@wiw_token%>");
$result = $wiw->post("account/11/invite", array(
    "email_or_phone" => "9525551234",
    "manager_name" => "Sally Smith",
    "message" => "This scheduling app is really slick!",
));
?>
```

```shell
curl -X POST <%=@api_prefix%>/2/account/35/invite \
 -H "W-Token: <%=@wiw_token%>" \
 -data '{"email_or_phone":"sally@example.com","manager_name":"Sally Smith","message":"This scheduling app is really slick!"}'
```
```php
<?php
$wiw = new Wheniwork("<%=@wiw_token%>");
$result = $wiw->post("account/11/invite", array(
    "email_or_phone" => "sally@example.com",
    "manager_name" => "Sally Smith",
    "message" => "This scheduling app is really slick!",
));
?>
```

> Example Response

<% json do %>
{
  "success": true
}
<% end %>

### Parameters

A value for `email_or_phone` must be provided. If a phone number is used, it should be in [E164][e164] format.

Key | Description
--- | -----------
<% param "account_id" do %>ID of the account object.<% end %>
<% param "email_or_phone" do %>Email address or phone number of the manager.<% end %>
<% param "region" do %>Two letter country code of the phone number. This can be omitted if the phone number is in [E164][e164] format.<% end %>
<% param "manager_name" do %>The manager's name.<% end %>
<% param "message" do %>A custom message that will be added to the invite.<% end %>

[e164]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E.164


